{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864597527,"sessionID":"ses_28638dbeaffeVawnyVVR7h7E8m","part":{"id":"prt_d79c741cf001U3xaDpushV61MO","messageID":"msg_d79c734c10014039H6UxWAFVVp","sessionID":"ses_28638dbeaffeVawnyVVR7h7E8m","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a73558b0d6f047d3a3beae5a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI invoke and status commands in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-023\n10: - **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n11: - **Language**: Python\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Background\n17: \n18: The `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to deployed agents via the AgentCube Router or standard Kubernetes Service. The `status` command retrieves and displays the current status of deployed agents. Both commands work with either the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) or the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## Requirements\n23: \n24: ### AR-023-001: invoke CLI interface\n25: \n26: The system SHALL expose the `invoke` command via Typer with specific options.\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: AR-023-001-A — Invoke command options\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help`\n31: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n32:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n33:   - `--payload JSON` — JSON-formatted input passed to the agent (default: \"{}\")\n34:   - `--header KEY:VALUE` — Custom HTTP headers (repeatable)\n35:   - `--provider PROVIDER` — Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' (default: \"agentcube\")\n36:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: AR-023-001-B — Default options\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke` with no options\n41: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\n42:   - `workspace`: `\".\"`\n43:   - `payload`: `\"{}\"`\n44:   - `header_list`: `None`\n45:   - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n46:   - `verbose`: `False`\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ### AR-023-002: invoke payload parsing\n51: \n52: The system SHALL parse and validate the JSON payload.\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: AR-023-002-A — Valid JSON payload\n55: \n56: - **GIVEN** `--payload` contains valid JSON (e.g., `{\"message\": \"hello\"}`)\n57: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n58: - **THEN** the system SHALL convert it to a Python dict for the HTTP request body\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: AR-023-002-B — Invalid JSON payload\n61: \n62: - **GIVEN** `--payload` contains invalid JSON (e.g., `{invalid}`)\n63: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n64: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print \"Invalid JSON payload: {parse_error}\" in red\n65: - **AND** exit with code `1` before calling `_handle_error`\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: AR-023-002-C — Empty payload default\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke` without `--payload`\n70: - **WHEN** the command parses the default `\"{}\"`\n71: - **THEN** the system SHALL use an empty dict `{}` as the request body\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ### AR-023-003: invoke header parsing\n76: \n77: The system SHALL parse custom HTTP headers from the command line.\n78: \n79: #### Scenario: AR-023-003-A — Valid headers\n80: \n81: - **GIVEN** `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"` is provided\n82: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n83: - **THEN** the system SHALL add `{\"Authorization\": \"Bearer token\"}` to the request headers\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: AR-023-003-B — Multiple headers\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** multiple `--header` options are provided\n88: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n89: - **THEN** all headers SHALL be merged into the request\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: AR-023-003-C — Invalid header format\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator (e.g., `InvalidHeader`)\n94: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n95: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print \"Invalid header format: '{header}'. Expected key:value\" in red\n96: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: AR-023-003-D — Header with multiple colons\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** a header string with multiple colons (e.g., `Authorization: Bearer:token`)\n101: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n102: - **THEN** the system SHALL split on the first colon only, resulting in `{\"Authorization\": \"Bearer:token\"}`\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ### AR-023-004: invoke prerequisites\n107: \n108: The system SHALL validate invoke prerequisites before making requests.\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: AR-023-004-A — Validate workspace exists\n111: \n112: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n113: - **WHEN** invoke runs\n114: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: AR-023-004-B — Validate metadata exists\n117: \n118: - **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n119: - **WHEN** invoke runs\n120: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: AR-023-004-C — Validate agent is published\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id` (not published)\n125: - **WHEN** invoke runs\n126: - **THEN** the system SHALL print \"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\" in yellow\n127: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ### AR-023-005: invoke agentcube provider\n132: \n133: The system SHALL invoke agents via the AgentCube Router when provider is \"agentcube\".\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: AR-023-005-A — Get endpoint from metadata\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" and metadata contains `agent_endpoint`\n138: - **WHEN** `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` runs\n139: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the endpoint URL, namespace, and agent name\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: AR-023-005-B — Session header from metadata\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n144: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n145: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` with the session_id value\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: AR-023-005-C — URL rewrite for AgentRuntime\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"` in metadata\n150: - **WHEN** invoking the agent\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: AR-023-005-D — Missing router_url\n154: \n155: - **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" but metadata lacks `router_url`\n156: - **WHEN** invoke runs\n157: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message about missing router_url\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ### AR-023-006: invoke k8s provider\n162: \n163: The system SHALL invoke agents via Kubernetes Service when provider is \"k8s\".\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: AR-023-006-A — Get service URL from metadata\n166: \n167: - **GIVEN** provider is \"k8s\" and metadata contains `k8s_deployment.service_url`\n168: - **WHEN** invoke runs\n169: - **THEN** the system SHALL use that URL as the invocation endpoint\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: AR-023-006-B — Missing service URL\n172: \n173: - **GIVEN** provider is \"k8s\" but metadata lacks `k8s_deployment.service_url`\n174: - **WHEN** invoke runs\n175: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message about missing service_url\n176: \n177: ---\n178: \n179: ### AR-023-007: invoke HTTP request\n180: \n181: The system SHALL send HTTP requests to the agent endpoint.\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: AR-023-007-A — POST request with JSON body\n184: \n185: - **GIVEN** a valid endpoint and payload\n186: - **WHEN** the HTTP request is sent\n187: - **THEN** the system SHALL POST with `Content-Type: application/json` and body as JSON\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: AR-023-007-B — Response handling\n190: \n191: - **GIVEN** the agent returns a successful response\n192: - **WHEN** invoke completes\n193: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the response body (formatted if JSON)\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: AR-023-007-C — HTTP error handling\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** the agent returns an HTTP error (4xx/5xx)\n198: - **WHEN** invoke processes the response\n199: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print the error in red with status code\n200: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n201: \n202: ---\n203: \n204: ### AR-023-008: status CLI interface\n205: \n206: The system SHALL expose the `status` command via Typer with specific options.\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: AR-023-008-A — Status command options\n209: \n210: - **GIVEN** the user runs `kubectl-agentcube status --help`\n211: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display:\n212:   - `-f, --workspace PATH` — Path to agent workspace (default: \".\")\n213:   - `--provider PROVIDER` — Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' (default: \"agentcube\")\n214:   - `--verbose` — Enable detailed logging\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: AR-023-008-B — Default options\n217: \n218: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status` with no options\n219: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be applied:\n220:   - `workspace`: `\".\"`\n221:   - `provider`: `\"agentcube\"`\n222:   - `verbose`: `False`\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ### AR-023-009: status prerequisites\n227: \n228: The system SHALL validate status prerequisites before querying.\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: AR-023-009-A — Validate workspace exists\n231: \n232: - **GIVEN** the specified workspace path does not exist\n233: - **WHEN** status runs\n234: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n235: \n236: #### Scenario: AR-023-009-B — Validate metadata exists\n237: \n238: - **GIVEN** the workspace does not contain `agent_metadata.yaml`\n239: - **WHEN** status runs\n240: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `FileNotFoundError`\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ### AR-023-010: status not published\n245: \n246: The system SHALL handle the case where the agent has not been published.\n247: \n248: #### Scenario: AR-023-010-A — Not published status\n249: \n250: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n251: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n252: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print \"Agent has not been published. Run 'kubectl-agentcube publish' first.\" in yellow\n253: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ### AR-023-011: status agentcube provider\n258: \n259: The system SHALL retrieve AgentRuntime CR status when provider is \"agentcube\".\n260: \n261: #### Scenario: AR-023-011-A — CR exists with status\n262: \n263: - **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" and the AgentRuntime CR exists with status\n264: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n265: - **THEN** the system SHALL read `cr_object[\"status\"]` for `status` and `agentEndpoint`\n266: \n267: #### Scenario: AR-023-011-B — CR exists without status\n268: \n269: - **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" and the AgentRuntime CR exists but has no status field\n270: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n271: - **THEN** the system SHALL return status as \"created_no_status\"\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: AR-023-011-C — CR not found\n274: \n275: - **GIVEN** provider is \"agentcube\" and the AgentRuntime CR does not exist\n276: - **WHEN** `_get_cr_k8s_status` runs\n277: - **THEN** the system SHALL return status as \"not_found_in_k8s\"\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ### AR-023-012: status k8s provider\n282: \n283: The system SHALL retrieve Kubernetes Deployment status when provider is \"k8s\".\n284: \n285: #### Scenario: AR-023-012-A — Deployment status\n286: \n287: - **GIVEN** provider is \"k8s\" and the Deployment exists\n288: - **WHEN** `_get_k8s_status` runs\n289: - **THEN** the system SHALL return deployment status including:\n290:   - Available replicas\n291:   - Ready replicas\n292:   - Namespace\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: AR-023-012-B — Deployment not found\n295: \n296: - **GIVEN** provider is \"k8s\" and the Deployment does not exist\n297: - **WHEN** `_get_k8s_status` runs\n298: - **THEN** the system SHALL return status as \"not_found\"\n299: \n300: ---\n301: \n302: ### AR-023-013: status output display\n303: \n304: The system SHALL display status information using Rich formatting.\n305: \n306: #### Scenario: AR-023-013-A — Status table display\n307: \n308: - **GIVEN** status is retrieved successfully\n309: - **WHEN** the command displays results\n310: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use a Rich `Table` with columns:\n311:   - Field\n312:   - Value\n313: - **AND** display: Agent Name, Provider, Status, Endpoint/Service URL\n314: \n315: #### Scenario: AR-023-013-B — Status error exit\n316: \n317: - **GIVEN** status is `\"not_published\"` or `\"error\"`\n318: - **WHEN** the command runs\n319: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL exit with code `1`\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ### AR-023-014: Error handling\n324: \n325: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate error messages and exit codes.\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: AR-023-014-A — Invoke error with verbose logging\n328: \n329: - **GIVEN** invoke raises an exception\n330: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n331: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n332: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: AR-023-014-B — Status error with verbose logging\n335: \n336: - **GIVEN** status raises an exception\n337: - **WHEN** `--verbose` flag is enabled\n338: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print error message in red with full traceback\n339: - **AND** exit with code `1`\n340: \n341: ---\n342: \n343: ## Acceptance Criteria\n344: \n345: - [ ] AC001: Invoke command accepts all specified CLI options (workspace, payload, header, provider, verbose)\n346: - [ ] AC002: Invoke validates JSON payload and exits with code 1 for invalid JSON\n347: - [ ] AC003: Invoke validates header format and exits with code 1 for invalid headers\n348: - [ ] AC004: Invoke adds session header (X-Agentcube-Session-Id) when session_id exists in metadata\n349: - [ ] AC005: Invoke validates agent is published before attempting to invoke\n350: - [ ] AC006: Invoke rewrites URL for AgentRuntime CR deployments\n351: - [ ] AC007: Invoke sends POST request with JSON body and appropriate headers\n352: - [ ] AC008: Status command accepts all specified CLI options (workspace, provider, verbose)\n353: - [ ] AC009: Status validates workspace and metadata exist before proceeding\n354: - [ ] AC010: Status returns \"not_published\" and exits with code 1 when agent not published\n355: - [ ] AC011: Status retrieves AgentRuntime CR status for agentcube provider\n356: - [ ] AC012: Status retrieves Deployment status for k8s provider\n357: - [ ] AC013: Status displays results in Rich Table format\n358: - [ ] AC014: Both commands handle errors with appropriate exit codes and verbose logging\n359: \n360: ---\n361: \n362: ## Architecture Notes\n363: \n364: ### Key Components\n365: \n366: | Component | Path | Description |\n367: |-----------|------|-------------|\n368: | CLI Entry | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer app with `invoke` and `status` commands |\n369: | InvokeRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | Core invoke logic |\n370: | StatusRuntime | `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | Core status logic |\n371: | MetadataService | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata CRUD operations |\n372: | AgentMetadata | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Metadata model with validators |\n373: \n374: ### Invoke Flow\n375: \n376: ```\n377: invoke command (provider=agentcube)\n378:     └─> InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n379:             ├─> _validate_invoke_prerequisites()\n380:             │       └─> Returns: endpoint, namespace, agent_name\n381:             └─> _invoke_agent_via_agentcube()\n382:                     └─> POST to router with session header\n383: \n384: invoke command (provider=k8s)\n385:     └─> InvokeRuntime.invoke()\n386:             └─> _direct_http_invocation()\n387:                     └─> POST to k8s service URL\n388: ```\n389: \n390: ### Status Flow\n391: \n392: ```\n393: status command (provider=agentcube)\n394:     └─> StatusRuntime.get_status()\n395:             └─> _get_cr_k8s_status()\n396:                     └─> Query AgentRuntime CR\n397: \n398: status command (provider=k8s)\n399:     └─> StatusRuntime.get_status()\n400:             └─> _get_k8s_status()\n401:                     └─> Query Deployment/Service\n402: ```\n403: \n404: ### CLI Options Mapping\n405: \n406: | Command | CLI Option | Runtime Parameter | Type |\n407: |---------|------------|-------------------|------|\n408: | invoke | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n409: | invoke | `--payload` | payload | str (JSON) |\n410: | invoke | `--header` | header_list | Optional[List[str]] |\n411: | invoke | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n412: | invoke | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n413: | status | `-f, --workspace` | workspace_path | str |\n414: | status | `--provider` | provider | str (default: \"agentcube\") |\n415: | status | `--verbose` | verbose | bool |\n416: \n417: ### Provider Types\n418: \n419: | Provider | Invocation Target | Status Target |\n420: |----------|-------------------|---------------|\n421: | `agentcube` | AgentRuntime CR via Router | AgentRuntime CR |\n422: | `k8s` | Kubernetes Service | Kubernetes Deployment |\n423: \n424: ---\n425: \n426: ## References\n427: \n428: - Base design: `cli-toolkit/design.md`\n429: - Base spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n430: - CLI entry point: `agentcube/cli/main.py`\n431: - InvokeRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n432: - StatusRuntime implementation: `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n433: - Metadata model: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n434: - AgentMetadata: `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n435: - Related: AR-022 (publish command)\n\n(End of file - total 435 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-023 — CLI invoke/status 命令\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the CLI invoke and status commands in the AgentCube CLI tool (`kubectl-agentcube`).\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-023\n- **Module**: `cmd/cli`\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: M\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nThe `invoke` command sends JSON payloads to deployed agents via the AgentCube Router or standard Kubernetes Service. The `status` command retrieves and displays the current status of deployed agents. Both commands work with either the AgentCube provider (AgentRuntime CR) or the standard Kubernetes provider (Deployment + Service).\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775864597498,"end":1775864597524}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775864597530,"sessionID":"ses_28638dbeaffeVawnyVVR7h7E8m","part":{"id":"prt_d79c74706001Uit5Sfs9C1oNni","messageID":"msg_d79c734c10014039H6UxWAFVVp","sessionID":"ses_28638dbeaffeVawnyVVR7h7E8m","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9b7bfd5b2a514e469f49c8fb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command Tasks\n2: \n3: **AR:** AR-023  \n4: **Module:** cmd/cli  \n5: **Language:** Python  \n6: **Size:** M  \n7: \n8: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n9: \n10: ## Implementation Tasks\n11: \n12: ### Phase 1: CLI Interface Implementation\n13: - [ ] **T001** Implement `invoke` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` with options: `--workspace`, `--payload`, `--header`, `--provider`, `--verbose`\n14: - [ ] **T002** Implement `status` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` with options: `--workspace`, `--provider`, `--verbose`\n15: - [ ] **T003** Add `_handle_error` function for error formatting with verbose mode support\n16: \n17: ### Phase 2: Runtime Implementation\n18: - [ ] **T004** Implement `InvokeRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n19: - [ ] **T005** Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` method in InvokeRuntime (AR-023-004)\n20: - [ ] **T006** Implement `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` with session header support (AR-023-005-B)\n21: - [ ] **T007** Implement URL rewrite for AgentRuntime CR deployments (AR-023-005-C)\n22: - [ ] **T008** Implement `_direct_http_invocation` for k8s provider (AR-023-006)\n23: - [ ] **T009** Implement `StatusRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n24: - [ ] **T010** Implement `_get_cr_k8s_status` for AgentCube provider (AR-023-011)\n25: - [ ] **T011** Implement `_get_k8s_status` for standard k8s provider (AR-023-012)\n26: \n27: ### Phase 3: Provider Integration\n28: - [ ] **T012** Add `get_agent_status` method to `KubernetesProvider` (AR-023-012-A)\n29: - [ ] **T013** Add `get_agent_runtime` method to `AgentCubeProvider` (AR-023-011)\n30: \n31: ### Phase 4: Input Validation\n32: - [ ] **T014** Validate workspace path exists (AR-023-004-A)\n33: - [ ] **T015** Validate metadata file exists (AR-023-004-B)\n34: - [ ] **T016** Validate agent is published before invoke (AR-023-004-C)\n35: - [ ] **T017** Validate JSON payload parsing (AR-023-002-A/B/C)\n36: - [ ] **T018** Validate header format with colon split (AR-023-003-A/B/C/D)\n37: \n38: ### Phase 5: HTTP Request/Response\n39: - [ ] **T019** Send POST request with JSON body (AR-023-007-A)\n40: - [ ] **T020** Handle success response (2xx) (AR-023-007-B)\n41: - [ ] **T021** Handle HTTP error response (4xx/5xx) (AR-023-007-C)\n42: \n43: ### Phase 6: Output Display\n44: - [ ] **T022** Display status in Rich Table format (AR-023-013-A)\n45: - [ ] **T023** Return appropriate exit codes for errors (AR-023-013-B)\n46: \n47: ### Phase 7: Testing\n48: - [ ] **T024** Write unit tests for `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` with valid payload\n49: - [ ] **T025** Write unit tests for `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` with invalid JSON payload\n50: - [ ] **T026** Write unit tests for header parsing (AR-023-003-A/B/C/D)\n51: - [ ] **T027** Write unit tests for `StatusRuntime.get_status()` with agentcube provider\n52: - [ ] **T028** Write unit tests for `StatusRuntime.get_status()` with k8s provider\n53: - [ ] **T029** Write unit tests for not-published scenario (AR-023-010-A)\n54: - [ ] **T030** Add CLI integration tests for `invoke` command using CliRunner\n55: - [ ] **T031** Add CLI integration tests for `status` command using CliRunner\n56: \n57: ### Phase 8: Documentation\n58: - [ ] **T032** Document CLI usage for invoke command\n59: - [ ] **T033** Document CLI usage for status command\n60: \n61: ## Verification Criteria\n62: \n63: - [ ] **VC001** `kubectl-agentcube invoke --help` shows all required options\n64: - [ ] **VC002** `kubectl-agentcube status --help` shows all required options\n65: - [ ] **VC003** Invoke returns exit code 1 for invalid JSON payload\n66: - [ ] **VC004** Invoke returns exit code 1 for invalid header format\n67: - [ ] **VC005** Invoke adds X-Agentcube-Session-Id header when session_id exists\n68: - [ ] **VC006** Invoke returns exit code 1 when agent not published\n69: - [ ] **VC007** Status returns \"not_published\" and exit code 1 when agent not published\n70: - [ ] **VC008** Status displays Rich Table with agent info\n71: - [ ] **VC009** All unit tests pass\n72: - [ ] **VC010** CLI integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 72 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Command Tasks\n\n**AR:** AR-023  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n\n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design Completed)\n\n## Implementation Tasks\n\n### Phase 1: CLI Interface Implementation\n- [ ] **T001** Implement `invoke` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` with options: `--workspace`, `--payload`, `--header`, `--provider`, `--verbose`\n- [ ] **T002** Implement `status` command in `agentcube/cli/main.py` with options: `--workspace`, `--provider`, `--verbose`\n- [ ] **T003** Add `_handle_error` function for error formatting with verbose mode support\n\n### Phase 2: Runtime Implementation\n- [ ] **T004** Implement `InvokeRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n- [ ] **T005** Implement `_validate_invoke_prerequisites` method in InvokeRuntime (AR-023-004)\n- [ ] **T006** Implement `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube` with session header support (AR-023-005-B)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-023/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775864597502,"end":1775864597528}}}}
